Feature codes:

Scenario 1: No islands or tributaries
- Top left = TL_1
- Bottom left = BL_1
- Thalweg = t
- Bottom right = BR_1
- Top right = TR_1

Scenario 2: One island
- Top left = TL_1
- Bottom left = BL_1
- Thalweg = t
- Bottom right island = BRI_1
- Top right island = TRI_1
- Top left island = TLI_1
- Bottom left island = BLI_1
- Secondary thalweg = st_1
- Bottom right = BR_1
- Top right = TR_1

Scenario 3: Two (or more) overlapping islands
- Top left = TL_1
- Bottom left = BL_1
- Thalweg = t
- Bottom right island = BRI_1
- Top right island = TRI_1
- Top left island = TLI_1
- Bottom left island = BLI_1
- Secondary thalweg = st_1
- Bottom right island = BRI_2
- Top right island = TRI_2
- Top left island = TLI_2
- Bottom left island = BLI_2
- Secondary thalweg = st_2
- Bottom right = BR_1
- Top right = TR_1

Scenario 4: One bank forms a peninsula-like feature
- Top left = TL_1
- Bottom left = BL_1
- Thalweg = t
- Bottom right = BR_1
- Top right = TR_1
- Top right = TRP_1
- Top right = TRP_2

Scenario 5: A part of the channel is disconnected from the mainstem
- Top left = TL_1
- Bottom left = BL_1
- Thalweg = t
- Bottom right = BR_1
- Top right = TR_1
- TLD_1
- TRD_1

Scenario 6: Some banks may be coded as EOV
- EOV on left bank = EOVL
- EOV on right bank = EOVR
- EOV on right of island = EOVR_1
- EOV on left of island = EOVL_1
- EOV on right of second island = EOVR_2
- EOV on left of second island = EOVL_2

Scenario 7: Some overbank shots may have been surveyed beyond top-of-bank or edge-of-veg
- Left valley bottom shot = VL
- Right valley bottom shot = VR
- First island = VI_1
- Second island = VI_2